question: The main source of food for a coyote population in one area is mice. Which is most likely to happen to these coyotes if a new predator begins eating the mice?
candidate_answers: (A) There will be fewer coyotes. (B) The coyotes will produce more young. (C) More coyotes will arrive from other locations. (D) Each coyote will spend less time hunting food.
answer: More coyotes will arrive from other locations.
label: C
